The Story Of How We Got Hollow Knight:

So Axo had this AI Windows Emulator (he refers to this as "AI Google") that could unblock things, sadly we don't have the windows emulator file anymore,
but Axo found a Hollow Knight website on the emulator and started to experiment with it later on.

"I have found a fake Hollow Knight! Search Hollow Knight in the AI Google thing, then scroll down. You’ll see something called hollowknight.io or smth.
Wait, I'm testing this out. This is a cool version, can’t believe it worked."
"OMG THIS IS LITERALLY A LESS GRAPHICS INTENSIVE PORT OF THE GAME. IT'S THE REAL GAME BUT IN A WEBSITE…"

Creep was on at the time and kept trying to get to the site on the windows emulator on chromebook, but apparently it didn't work.
"It says it refused to connect." 
Axo and Creep trying to troubleshoot the problem:
"Maybe reopen Google? It worked just fine before. Also, I got Google and YouTube to connect. I just had to try a couple times, and with a couple other links. 
It should work eventually."
"I don’t think some of the websites work on chromebooks, for one it said it was blocked"
"Oh. idk then I’ll troubleshoot the google thing a little."
Eventually Axo basically found out how it worked:
"OK, so the hollow knight site actually doesn’t work on a chromebook, since it is rendered as an embedded site, so I will try and find a good site to use with the AI google 
that actually has hollow knight. :) ...However, I haven’t tested it on a chromebook. Only my home PC."
